<Base title="Dayroll — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/dayroll/">← Dayroll</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 2, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Dayroll collects nothing. We can't read your journal, and we don't want to.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Everything you write in Dayroll is stored locally on your device. If iCloud sync is
     enabled, entries are synced through your personal iCloud account using Apple's CloudKit —
     encrypted in transit and at rest, accessible only to you. Your data never touches our servers,
     because we don't have any.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No accounts. No analytics. No ads. No third-party SDKs. No tracking of any kind.</p>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>The one-time unlock is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We never see your
     payment details.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/dayroll/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
